definition: to pile up/to heap up/a mass/pile/heap/stack/large amount

sentences.english: The room is lumbered up with useless articles.
sentences.chinese: 房间时堆满了无用的东西。

sentences.english: The cart was piled high with fruit and vegetables.
sentences.chinese: 大车上高高地堆满了水果和蔬菜。

sentences.english: The room was encumbered with old furniture.
sentences.chinese: 这间屋子堆满了旧家具。

sentences.english: Completing the war motif, sandbags surround the outdoor seating area.
sentences.chinese: 为了凸显战争主题，店外客座区周围都堆满了沙袋。

sentences.english: The shelves in the supermarket is full of items before the Christmas rush.
sentences.chinese: 圣诞争购热潮前超市市场的货架堆满了商品。

sentences.english: The cloud-mussed sky turned a vague copper color.
sentences.chinese: 堆满乌云的天空现出一种混沌的紫铜色。

sentences.english: Puffy, plasticky packages of Doggie Depends stocked in the pantry.
sentences.chinese: 橱柜堆满鼓鼓的塑料包装狗尿布。

sentences.english: Books covered the tables and were piled up on the floor. A simple wooden bed stood in a corner.
sentences.chinese: 桌上和地板上都堆满了书，墙角是一张简单的木床。

sentences.english: The room was encumbered with heavy furniture.
sentences.chinese: 房内堆满了笨重的家具。

sentences.english: People posted critcisms on my blog.
sentences.chinese: 我的博客里堆满了人们的批评帖。

sentences.english: The vacant apartments were full of refuse that had not been carted away.
sentences.chinese: 空着的公寓里堆满了还没有被运走的垃圾。

sentences.english: The archives were filled to the rafters with piles of manually labeled videocassettes.
sentences.chinese: 贴有人工手写标签的录像带堆满了档案柜。

sentences.english: So, they dug a lot of the roots and pile them in the hole.
sentences.chinese: 两人就挖了很多，堆满半个树洞。

sentences.english: Its rusted banks are piled with junk and trash.
sentences.chinese: 锈迹斑斑的河岸两边堆满了垃圾和废物。

sentences.english: The room was filled with cases of liquor.
sentences.chinese: 房间里堆满了成箱的酒。

sentences.english: The bay (image right) is filled with slush and icebergs from the collapsed shelf.
sentences.chinese: 图右侧的海湾中堆满了冰架崩塌后留下的积雪和冰山。
